 from the past fifty years, from Planet of the Apes to I Am Mother. It offers unique, clearly presented insights into recurring patterns that appear in an extraordinarily ubiquitous genre that has only increased in popularity, and whose themes of racial anxiety are increasingly pertinent in our increasingly contentious political climate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aApocalyptic filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aRace in motion pictures. 0aRace relations in motion pictures. 0aWhite people in motion pictures. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848945240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438489452423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438489452/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles